{"title_page": "COVID-19 pandemic in Switzerland", "text_new": "{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Switzerland}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = COVID-19 pandemic in Switzerland\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Switzerland by Canton.svg\n| legend1         = {{center|Map of cantons in Switzerland by number of confirmed cases (as of 1 May)<ref name=\"Cases by Canton\">{{cite news|url=https://interactif.tdg.ch/2020/covid-19-carte-suisse/|title=Cas d'infection au Sars-CoV-2 en Suisse|date=18 March 2020|publisher=[[Tribune de Gen\u00e8ve]]|language=fr|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319122918/https://interactif.tdg.ch/2020/covid-19-carte-suisse/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>}} {{legend|#FFCECD|1-99 cases}} {{legend|#F28786|100-499 cases}} {{legend|#D42016|500-999 cases}} {{legend|#A31508|1,000-2,499 cases}} {{legend|#630800|2,500+ cases}}\n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Switzerland]]\n| first_case      = [[Lugano]], [[Ticino]]\n| arrival_date    = 25 February 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=02|day1=25|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]] via [[Milan]], [[Italy]]\n| recovery_cases  = 25,200<ref name=\"TribunedeGeneve\">{{Cite web|url=https://interactif.tdg.ch/2020/covid-19-carte-suisse/|title=Cas d'infection au Sars-CoV-2 en Suisse}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 1,775<ref name=\"bag.admin.ch\">https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/situation-schweiz-und-international.html#-6104062</ref><ref name=\"TribunedeGeneve\"/>\n| confirmed_cases = 29,773<ref name=\"bag.admin.ch\">https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/situation-schweiz-und-international.html#-6104062</ref><ref name=\"TribunedeGeneve\"/>\n| website         = [https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov.html BAG Schweiz]\n}}\n\nThe [[COVID-19 pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread to [[Switzerland]] on 25 February 2020 when the first case of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] was confirmed following a [[COVID-19 pandemic in Italy|COVID-19 outbreak in Italy]]. A 70-year-old man in the Italian-speaking [[canton of Ticino]] which borders Italy, tested positive for SARS-CoV-2. The man had previously visited [[Milan]].<ref name=\"Switzerland_de22\">{{cite news|url=https://www.blick.ch/news/coronavirus-erster-bestaetigter-fall-von-coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-id15767285.html|title=Erster best\u00e4tigter Fall in der Schweiz|date=25 February 2020|publisher=[[Blick]]|language=de|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227232503/https://www.blick.ch/news/coronavirus-erster-bestaetigter-fall-von-coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-id15767285.html|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Switzerland_Ticinto2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thelocal.ch/20200225/breaking|title=BREAKING: Switzerland confirms first case of coronavirus|date=25 February 2020|publisher=[[The Local]]|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227141321/https://www.thelocal.ch/20200225/breaking|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Afterwards, multiple cases related to the Italy clusters were discovered in multiple cantons, including [[Basel-City]], Z\u00fcrich, and Graub\u00fcnden.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788|title=Coronavirus cases spreading in Switzerland|author=|website=[[Swissinfo]]|language=en|access-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227084453/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx|title=Informationen zum Coronavirus|website=www.gr.ch|access-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227101110/https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167|title=Swiss coronavirus cases rise to nine as children placed in precautionary quarantine|date=2020-02-27|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-29|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228072103/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Multiple isolated cases not related to the Italy clusters were also subsequently confirmed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/google-employee-zurich-office-tests-191438904.html|title=Google employee who was at Zurich office tests positive for coronavirus|website=finance.yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228193637/https://finance.yahoo.com/news/google-employee-zurich-office-tests-191438904.html|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, the national government, the [[Federal Council (Switzerland)|Federal Council]], banned all events with more than 1,000 participants. On 16 March, schools and most shops were closed nationwide, and on 20 March, all gatherings of more than five people in public spaces were banned. Additionally, the government gradually imposed restrictions on border crossings and announced economic support measures worth 40 billion Swiss francs.<ref>{{Cite news|last=NZZ-Redaktion|url=https://www.nzz.ch/schweiz/coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-die-neusten-entwicklungen-ld.1542664|title=Coronavirus in der Schweiz: die neusten Entwicklungen|work=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung|access-date=2020-03-20|language=de|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320161907/https://www.nzz.ch/schweiz/coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-die-neusten-entwicklungen-ld.1542664|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, who had initially come to the attention of the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=\"Elsevier\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center|last=Elsevier|date=|website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Reynolds4March2020\">{{Cite news|last=Reynolds|first=Matt|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic?|date=4 March 2020|work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|issn=1357-0978}}</ref>\n\nUnlike [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]], the [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 <ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus|website=Imperial News|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England|last=|first=|date=|website=GOV.UK|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> has been much lower, but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=\"WFSA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" />\n\n==Timeline==\n\n=== February 2020 ===\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Switzerland medical cases chart}}\n\nOn 25 February 2020, [[Switzerland]] confirmed the first case of COVID-19, a 70-year-old man in the Italian-speaking [[canton of Ticino]] bordering Italy, who had previously visited Milan tested positive for SARS-CoV-2.<ref name=\"Switzerland\">{{cite news|url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-updates-us-criticizes-iran-and-china-over-the-their-handling-of-the-outbreak/a-52516885|title=Coronavirus updates: US criticizes Iran and China over the their handling of the outbreak|date=25 February 2020|publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]]|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225161221/https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-updates-us-criticizes-iran-and-china-over-the-their-handling-of-the-outbreak/a-52516885|archive-date=25 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Switzerland_de2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.blick.ch/news/coronavirus-erster-bestaetigter-fall-von-coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-id15767285.html|title=Erster best\u00e4tigter Fall in der Schweiz|language=de|date=25 February 2020|publisher=[[Blick]]|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227232503/https://www.blick.ch/news/coronavirus-erster-bestaetigter-fall-von-coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-id15767285.html|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Switzerland_Ticinto2\"/>\n\nOn 27 February, a 28-year-old IT worker from [[Geneva]], who had recently returned from Milan, tested positive and was admitted to the [[Geneva University Hospitals|Geneva University Hospital]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/das-bag/aktuell/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78268.html|title=New coronavirus Covid-19: three new confirmed cases in Switzerland|website=www.bag.admin.ch|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227113237/https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/das-bag/aktuell/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78268.html|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=SWI27.02.2020/> A 55-year-old Italian who worked in an international company also tested positive in Geneva.<ref name=\":21\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rts.ch/info/suisse/11127000-manifestations-d-ampleur-interdites-en-raison-du-coronavirus-conference-de-presse-du-conseil-federal-en-direct.html|title=Manifestations d'ampleur interdites en raison du coronavirus. Conf\u00e9rence de presse du Conseil f\u00e9d\u00e9ral en direct|language=fr|website=rts.ch|date=28 February 2020|access-date=28 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228094931/https://www.rts.ch/info/suisse/11127000-manifestations-d-ampleur-interdites-en-raison-du-coronavirus-conference-de-presse-du-conseil-federal-en-direct.html|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Two Italian children, who were on vacation in [[Canton of Grisons|Graub\u00fcnden]], tested positive and were hospitalised.<ref name=SWI27.02.2020>{{Cite web|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788|title=Switzerland confirms total of four coronavirus cases|author=|website=[[Swissinfo]]|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227084453/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx|title=Informationen zum Coronavirus|website=www.gr.ch|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227101110/https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=BielerTagblatt>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bielertagblatt.ch/nachrichten/schweiz/graubuenden-sagt-den-engadiner-skimarathon-ab|author=Swiss Telegraphic Agency|title=Graub\u00fcnden sagt den Engadiner Skimarathon ab|website=www.bielertagblatt.ch|language=de|access-date=2020-02-27|author-link=Swiss Telegraphic Agency|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227174547/https://www.bielertagblatt.ch/nachrichten/schweiz/graubuenden-sagt-den-engadiner-skimarathon-ab|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nA 26-year-old man in [[Canton of Aargau|Aargau]], who had gone on a business trip the week before and stayed in [[Verona]], tested positive and was hospitalised.<ref name=SWI27.02.2020/> A 30-year-old woman, who had visited Milan, was admitted to a hospital in [[Z\u00fcrich|Zurich]].<ref name=\"SWI27.02.2020\"/> A 49-year-old man living in [[France]] and working in Vaud was confirmed positive in [[Vaud]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vd.ch/toutes-les-autorites/departements/departement-des-institutions-et-de-la-securite-dis/police-cantonale-vaudoise-polcant/medias/communiques-de-presse/news/12503i-coronavirus-premier-cas-detecte-dans-le-canton-de-vaud/|title=Coronavirus : premier cas d\u00e9tect\u00e9 dans le canton de Vaud|website=www.vd.ch|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227213534/https://www.vd.ch/toutes-les-autorites/departements/departement-des-institutions-et-de-la-securite-dis/police-cantonale-vaudoise-polcant/medias/communiques-de-presse/news/12503i-coronavirus-premier-cas-detecte-dans-le-canton-de-vaud/|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA young woman, who had travelled to Milan, tested positive in [[Canton of Basel-Stadt|Basel-Stadt]]. She worked in a daycare centre in [[Riehen]], and after her test had been confirmed, the children at the daycare were put into a two-week quarantine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167|title=Swiss coronavirus cases rise to nine as children placed in precautionary quarantine|date=2020-02-27|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-28|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228072103/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 February, her partner, a 23-year-old man, also tested positive in [[Canton of Basel-Landschaft|Basel-Landschaft]].<ref name=\":21\" />\n\n=== March 2020 ===\nOn 3 March, the [[University of Zurich]] announced six confirmed cases of coronavirus at the Institute of Mathematics. As of 5 March, there are 10 confirmed cases at the University of Zurich, at least 7 at the I-Math and 1 at the Center of Dental Medicine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.su.uzh.ch/en/Coronavirus.html|work=UZH|title=Coronavirus COVID-19|access-date=2020-03-03|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303185246/https://www.su.uzh.ch/en/Coronavirus.html|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 March, the [[Lausanne University Hospital]] announced that a 74-year-old female coronavirus case had died overnight.<ref name=\"vd.1\">{{Cite web | url=https://www.vd.ch/toutes-les-autorites/departements/departement-des-institutions-et-de-la-securite-dis/police-cantonale-vaudoise-polcant/medias/communiques-de-presse/news/12542i-coronavirus-ler-deces-dans-le-canton-de-vaud/ |title = Coronavirus : 1er d\u00e9c\u00e8s dans le canton de Vaud &#124; \u00c9tat de Vaud}}</ref> The patient had been hospitalised since 3 March, and had been suffering from chronic illness.<ref name=\"vd.1\"/>\n\nOn 11 March, a 54-year-old male died from COVID-19 in the [[Bruderholz]] Hospital in [[Canton of Basel-Landschaft|Basel-Landschaft]], marking the fourth fatal case in Switzerland. He had joined a religious event in [[Mulhouse]], [[France]] previous to contracting the virus and suffering from [[pneumonia]].<ref name=\"death4\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.20min.ch/schweiz/news/story/Coronavirus-News-Schweiz-29691128 |title=Berset-Challenge erreicht 1,4 Millionen Menschen |access-date=11 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302111128/https://www.20min.ch/schweiz/news/story/Coronavirus-News-Schweiz-29691128 |archive-date=2 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Government response==\n[[File:BAG Plakat CoVi QR Abstand A3 297x420 d Poppler.svg|thumb|left|Official poster explaining hygiene rules and correct reaction in case of symptoms (version of 5 March 2020)]]\n[[File:CoViD-19 CH.svg|thumb|upright=2|Number of cases (blue) and number of deaths (red) on a [[logarithmic scale]].]]\n\nOn 27 February, following the confirmation of COVID-19 cases in the region, [[Canton of Grisons|Graub\u00fcnden]] cancelled the [[Engadin Skimarathon|Engadine Skimarathon]].<ref name=BielerTagblatt/>\n\nOn 28 February, the Federal Council banned events involving more than 1,000 people in an effort to curb the spread of the infection.<ref name=\"bag\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov.html |title=New coronavirus |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302094217/https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov.html |archive-date=2 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.admin.ch/gov/en/start/documentation/media-releases.msg-id-78289.html | title=Coronavirus: Federal Council bans large-scale events | access-date=29 February 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229141218/https://www.admin.ch/gov/en/start/documentation/media-releases.msg-id-78289.html | archive-date=29 February 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref> Multiple events such as carnivals and fairs were either postponed or cancelled. [[Geneva Motor Show]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/motori/sezioni/attualita/2020/02/28/news/coronavirus_annullato_il_salone_dell_auto_di_ginevra-249789267/|title=Coronavirus, annullato il Salone dell'automobile di Ginevra|date=2020-02-28|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229003901/https://www.repubblica.it/motori/sezioni/attualita/2020/02/28/news/coronavirus_annullato_il_salone_dell_auto_di_ginevra-249789267/|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Baselworld]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.baselworld.com/en/news/news/2020-02-baselworld-communication|title=Baselworld postponed to January 2021|website=www.baselworld.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229072512/https://www.baselworld.com/en/news/news/2020-02-baselworld-communication|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Bern Carnival and the [[Carnival of Basel]] were cancelled.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/coronavirus_switzerland-bans-events-with-more-than-1-000-people/45585378|title=Switzerland bans major public events to slow spread of virus|author=|website=[[Swissinfo]]|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228234824/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/coronavirus_switzerland-bans-events-with-more-than-1-000-people/45585378|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> University of Bern replaced all face-to-face lectures with more than 250 attendees with online lectures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unibe.ch/coronavirus/index_ger.html|title=Coronavirus|date=2020-02-25|website=Portal|access-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229012228/https://www.unibe.ch/coronavirus/index_ger.html|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March 2020, the Federal Council announced a 'changed strategy' with a focus on the protection of the most vulnerable individuals, i.e., older persons and persons with pre-existing conditions.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.admin.ch/gov/de/start/dokumentation/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78381.html |title=Coronavirus: Verst\u00e4rkter Schutz besonders gef\u00e4hrdeter Personen und Evaluation der wirtschaftlichen Auswirkungen |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307144622/https://www.admin.ch/gov/de/start/dokumentation/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78381.html |archive-date=7 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March 2020, the Federal Council decided to cancel classes in all educational establishments until 4 April 2020, and has banned all events (public or private) involving more than 100 people. It has also decided to partially close its borders and enacted border controls.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.lemessager.fr/6559/article/2020-03-13/coronavirus-la-suisse-ferme-aussi-ses-ecoles-et-renforce-le-controle-aux |title = Coronavirus : Il y aura des contr\u00f4les \u00e0 toutes les fronti\u00e8res suisses}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.lenouvelliste.ch/dossiers/coronavirus/articles/coronavirus-les-ecoles-fermees-dans-toute-la-suisse-les-reunions-de-plus-de-100-personnes-interdites-919189 |title = Coronavirus: Toutes les nouvelles du vendredi 13 mars}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.admin.ch/gov/de/start/dokumentation/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78437.html |title=Bundesrat versch\u00e4rft Massnahmen gegen das Coronavirus zum Schutz der Gesundheit und unterst\u00fctzt betroffene Branchen |access-date=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314134305/https://www.admin.ch/gov/de/start/dokumentation/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78437.html |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The canton of Vaud took more drastic measures, prohibiting all public and private gatherings with more than 50 people, and closing its educational establishments until 30 April.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.24heures.ch/vaud-regions/eleves-maison-defi-teleenseignement/story/19330082 |title=Les \u00e9l\u00e8ves \u00e0 la maison, le d\u00e9fi du t\u00e9l\u00e9enseignement |newspaper=VQH |date=13 March 2020 |access-date=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315052242/https://www.24heures.ch/vaud-regions/eleves-maison-defi-teleenseignement/story/19330082 |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live |last1=Collet |first1=C\u00e9cile }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.laliberte.ch/news-agence/detail/vaud-ferme-toutes-les-ecoles-du-canton/557223 |title = Vaud ferme toutes les \u00e9coles du canton}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March 2020, the Federal Council announced<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fnuTzODXLvw |title=Archived copy |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318111106/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fnuTzODXLvw |archive-date=18 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> further measures, and a revised ordinance.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/de/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Verordnung-2.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317231248/https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/de/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Verordnung-2.pdf |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/fr/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Ordonnance-2.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317231246/https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/fr/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Ordonnance-2.pdf |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/it/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Ordinanza-2.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317231245/https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/it/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Ordinanza-2.pdf |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Measures include the closure of bars, shops and other gathering places until 19 April, but leaves open certain essentials, such as grocery shops, pharmacies, (a reduced) public transport and the postal service.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/massnahmen-des-bundes.html |title=New coronavirus: Federal government measures |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304142833/https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/massnahmen-des-bundes.html |archive-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe government announced a 42 billion CHF rescue package for the economy, which includes money to replace lost wages for employed and self-employed people, short-term loans to businesses, delay for payments to the government, and support for cultural and sport organisations.<ref name=\"urlBund startet gr\u00f6sstes Rettungspaket der Schweizer Geschichte - Wirtschaft - tagesanzeiger.ch, tagesanzeiger.ch: Nichts verpassen\">{{cite news |url=https://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/wirtschaft/standardbund-startet-groesstes-rettungspaket-der-schweizer-geschichte/story/31151375 |title=Bund startet gr\u00f6sstes Rettungspaket der Schweizer Geschichte - Wirtschaft - tagesanzeiger.ch, tagesanzeiger.ch: Nichts verpassen |newspaper=Tages-Anzeiger |format= |accessdate=2020-03-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320202638/https://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/wirtschaft/standardbund-startet-groesstes-rettungspaket-der-schweizer-geschichte/story/31151375 |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, the government announced that no lockdown would be implemented, but all events or meetings over 5 people were prohibited. Economic activities would continue including construction.<ref name=\"urlEin Riesenpaket f\u00fcr die Wirtschaft, Einschr\u00e4nkung im Privaten - Schweiz: Standard - tagesanzeiger.ch, tagesanzeiger.ch: Nichts verpassen\">{{cite web |url=https://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/schweiz/standard/verhaengt-der-bundesrat-eine-ausgangssperre-ueber-das-land/story/23987451 |title=Ein Riesenpaket f\u00fcr die Wirtschaft, Einschr\u00e4nkung im Privaten - Schweiz: Standard - tagesanzeiger.ch, tagesanzeiger.ch: Nichts verpassen |format= |accessdate=2020-03-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320202644/https://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/schweiz/standard/verhaengt-der-bundesrat-eine-ausgangssperre-ueber-das-land/story/23987451 |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThose measures were prolonged until 26 April 2020.<ref>[https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/massnahmen-des-bundes.html Federal Office of Public Health]</ref>\n\nOn April 16, 2020, Switzerland announced that the country will ease restrictions in a three-step, gradual way. The first step will begin on 27 April, for those who work in close contact with others, but not in large numbers.  Surgeons, dentists, day care workers, hairdressers, massage and beauty salons can be opened with safety procedures applied.  DIY stores, garden centres, florists and food shops that also sell other goods can also be opened. The second step will begin on 11 May, assuming the first step is implemented without problems, at which time other shops and schools can be opened.  The third step begin on 8 June with the easing of restrictions on vocational schools, universities, museums, zoos and libraries.<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.rte.ie/news/coronavirus/2020/0416/1131999-switzerland-coronavirus/ |title=Switzerland announces gradual easing of Covid-19 restrictions |journal=RT\u00c9 News |date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{multiple image\n|width =\n|align = center\n|image1=Voie du Chariot.jpg|alt1=\n|image2=Voie du Chariot (Coronavirus).jpg|alt2=\n|footer = The [[Le Flon (Lausanne)|Flon]] in Lausanne before and during the COVID-19 outbreak.\n}}\n\n==Statistics==\n\nAs with most countries, the number of people actually infected with COVID-19 in Switzerland is likely to be much higher than the number of confirmed cases,<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Lau|first=Hien|last2=Khosrawipour|first2=Veria|last3=Kocbach|first3=Piotr|last4=Mikolajczyk|first4=Agata|last5=Ichii|first5=Hirohito|last6=Schubert|first6=Justyna|last7=Bania|first7=Jacek|last8=Khosrawipour|first8=Tanja|date=2020-03-14|title=Internationally lost COVID-19 cases|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1684118220300736|journal=Journal of Microbiology, Immunology and Infection|language=en|doi=10.1016/j.jmii.2020.03.013|pmid=32205091|pmc=7102572|issn=1684-1182}}</ref> especially as, since 6 March 2020, the Swiss government has had an official policy of not testing people with only mild symptoms.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.derbund.ch/schweiz/standard/bund-sucht-nicht-mehr-alle-coronainfizierten/story/20389898|title=Bund sucht nicht mehr alle Corona-Infizierten|work=Der Bund|access-date=2020-03-31|language=de|issn=0774-6156}}</ref>\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Switzerland medical cases}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=800\n|colors=#FF6347\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|x=25 Feb, 26 Feb, 27 Feb, 28 Feb, 29 Feb, 1 Mar, 2 Mar, 3 Mar, 4 Mar, 5 Mar, 6 Mar, 7 Mar, 8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar, 1 Apr, 2 Apr, 3 Apr, 4 Apr, 5 Apr, 6 Apr, 7 Apr, 8 Apr, 9 Apr, 10 Apr, 11 Apr, 12 Apr, 13 Apr, 14 Apr, 15 Apr, 16 Apr, 17 Apr\n|yAxisTitle=No. of cases\n|y=1,1,5,15,18,24,30,37,58,87,181,228,281,312,475,642,854,1125,1359,2195,2330,2650,3000,3860,4803,6069,6968,8009,8785,9712,10658,12161,13213,14336,15411,16108,17071,18192,19227,20201,21023,21575,22165,22711,23495,24229,24821,25220,25500,25754,26256,26652,26998 \n|y1Title=Confirmed cases\n|yGrid= |xGrid=\n}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|width=800\n|colors=#F46D43\n| showValues=offset:2\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|type=rect\n|x= 25 Feb, 26 Feb, 27 Feb, 28 Feb, 29 Feb, 1 Mar, 2 Mar, 3 Mar, 4 Mar, 5 Mar, 6 Mar, 7 Mar, 8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar, 1 Apr,2 Apr, 3 Apr, 4 Apr, 5 Apr, 6 Apr, 7 Apr, 8 Apr, 9 Apr, 10 Apr, 11 Apr, 12 Apr, 13 Apr, 14 Apr, 15 Apr, 16 Apr, 17 Apr\n|yAxisTitle=No. of new cases\n|legend=Legend\n|y1=1,0,4,10,3,6,6,7,21,29,94,47,53