mic in Europe]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|COVID-19 pandemic in Switzerland}}\n*[https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases] and [https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19 historical data] by [[Johns Hopkins University]]\n*[https://www.corona-data.ch/ Corona Data] \u2013 interactive historic map of cases in Switzerland\n*[https://corona.arrangy.com Worldwide Coronavirus Map, confirmed Cases] \u2013 map the route paths of coronavirus confirmed cases\n*[https://swiss.coronamapper.com Swiss CoronaMapper] \u2013 map with several updated statistics\n*[https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/ Worldometer, COVID-19 coronavirus pandemic] \u2013 Confirmed Cases and Deaths by Country, Territory, or Conveyance, updated daily at midnight GMT+0\n*[https://coronavirus-global.com/switzerland Coronavirus Switzerland updates and news]. Switzerland in Coronavirus Global international portal. Available in English, French, German and more.\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Switzerland|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Switzerland| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country|Switzerland]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Europe]]\n", "name_user": "RobertskySemi", "label": "safe", "comment": "bypass redirect, replaced:COVID-19 pandemicwas confirmed to have spread toSwitzerlandon 25 February 2020 when the first case ofCOVID-19was confirmed following a [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|COVID-19", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Switzerland"}
